name: User can navigate to different pages of results, or by clicking 'Next,' and 'Previous'
User can enter address manually and hit Qualify
User can expand the 'Address Validation' pane
User can expand the 'Service Availability' pane
User can search by address or GLID and hit Qualify
User can see all recent activities that have not expired
User can drill into the Address Details page by clicking the name or address of a request
Export file includes the following columns: Date Created, Name or Address, Status, Expires In
Table is default sorted to 'Date Created' = Descending
User can log in to the application
Within the 'Service Availability' pane, user can navigate between available products at current address
User can export their list of recent activities
User can select 'Choose File' to upload
User can download multiple templates dynamically
User can enter address manually and hit '+ Save & Continue'
User can search by address or GLID and hit '+ Save & Continue'
User can navigate back to Address Search page or Recent Activities page using the breadcrumbs
User can export the request details
